Brazil to Boost Tax on Credit Purchases Abroad, Estado Says

-- B y   I u r i   D a n t a s
-- 
2011-03-26T12:52:35Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-26/brazil-to-boost-tax-on-credit-purchases-abroad-estado-says.html
Brazilian president  Dilma Rousseff 
signed a decree raising taxes on credit card purchases overseas,
including Internet commerce, o Estado de S.Paulo newspaper
 reported , without saying how it obtained the information.  The decree, which may be published March 28 in the official
gazette, raises the so-called IOF tax to 6.38 percent from 2.38
percent, Estado said. Gross spending by Brazilians abroad rose
to $2.03 billion in the first two months this year, from $1.51
billion in the same period last year, the newspaper said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Iuri Dantas in Brasilia at 
 idantas@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
 Joshua Goodman  at 
 jgoodman19@bloomberg.net . 